4 Sep 2015 Liberia: Oxfam launches Ebola recovery program
http://allafrica.com/stories/201509041727.html
[As part of efforts to complement Government's Ebola Recovery Plan, Oxfam Liberia has launched a USD 1.7 million Livelihood Program. The program, which was launched Mon [31 Aug 2015] in Mehnpa, Saclepea-Mah District, Nimba County, targets 11 317 beneficiaries from Nimba, River Gee and Grand Gedeh Counties.

The Cash for Work focuses on providing incentives to local farmers in the 3 counties, including farming implements. It also targets vulnerable persons in the 3 counties with a Livelihood Sustainable Grant of USD 150 to each beneficiary. Most of the beneficiaries include the elderly and persons with disabilities.

Oxfam Liberia Country Director Mamudu Salifu said the grant is aimed at strengthening the capacity of local farmers, women groups, and the vulnerable. Mr. Salifu revealed that the investigation shows that about 70 percent of Liberians could not provide for themselves and families due to the pandemic...more]

